ll be changed accordingly.  If there are any questions, please contact Student Employment at: (312) 996-3130.      Offices Associated With Student Employment        Job Center          Department          Payroll          Finding Student Employees        What can your department afford?          Choosing the appropriate title          Advertising to fill the position          General student eligibility          International Students          Hiring of Student Employees        Job orders          Assigning classifications and pay rates          Required paperwork          Health evaluations          Paper flow          Rehiring procedures          Payroll Processing        Daily Time Reports          Submitting time/ Payroll adjustments          Earning transfers          Record Keeping and Monitoring Requirements        Time records          Record retention          Federal Work-Study program monitoring          Enrollment monitoring          Class schedule monitoring          Work hours / Overtime          Pay Rises and Reclassifications        Raises          Reclassifications          New positions          Federal Work Study Program        General requirements          Application procedures and application dates          Awards, acceptance, and revisions          Monitoring earnings          Unused portion of previous semesters Federal Work/          Employers' Responsibilities to its Student Employees        General Guidelines          Meal Breaks and Rest Periods          Student Employees' Responsibilities to Employers          Student Wage Plan          Student Job Description          Appendixes/Forms              Departments    Back to main content           Hiring Procedures    Job Descriptions    Handbook    Forms    Student Wage Plan    FAQs                  UIC Logo        Student Employment         Quick Links    UIC Career Services    UIC Careers      For Students    Job Listings    JLD Program      For Departments    Forms    Job Descriptions   